<h1 id="date-picker">Date Picker</h1>
<p>Allows for the selection of a date into a text field.</p>
<h2 id="variants">Variants</h2>
<h3 id="default">Default</h3>

{{> DatePicker}}

<h2 id="states">States</h2>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>State</th>
            <th>Applied to</th>
            <th>Result</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>.is-highlighted</code></td>
            <td><code>.ms-DatePicker-monthOption</code>, <code>.ms-DatePicker-yearOption</code></td>
            <td>Marks a month or year as selected.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>.is-pickingYears</code></td>
            <td><code>.ms-DatePicker</code></td>
            <td>Displays a set of years to choose from.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>.is-pickingMonths</code></td>
            <td><code>.ms-DatePicker</code></td>
            <td>Displays a set of months to choose from.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<h2 id="using-this-component">Using this component</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Confirm that you have references to Fabric&#39;s CSS and JavaScript on your page, as well as jQuery and PickaDate.js library:<pre><code> &lt;head&gt;
     &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;fabric.min.css&quot;&gt;
     &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;fabric.components.min.css&quot;&gt;
     &lt;script src=&quot;jquery-2.2.1.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
     &lt;script src=&quot;fabric.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
     &lt;script src=&quot;PickaDate.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
 &lt;/head&gt;
</code></pre></li>
    <li>Copy the HTML from one of the samples above into your page. For example:
        <pre>
 <code>
{{renderPartialPre "DatePicker" "DatePickerExample" "" false}}
 </code>
</pre>
    </li>
    <li>Add the following <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag to your page, below the references to PickaDate and Fabric&#39;s JS, to instantiate all DatePicker components on the page:
        <pre>
 <code>
{{renderPartialPre "DatePicker" "DatePickerExampleJS" "" false}}
 </code>
</pre>
    </li>
    <li>Verify that the component is working the same as in the sample above.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="dependencies">Dependencies</h2>
<p>This component has no dependencies on other components. It does, however, require <a href="https://github.com/amsul/pickadate.js/releases/tag/3.5.3">pickadate.js 3.5.3</a>. Once you have downloaded the ZIP, you&#39;ll find <code>picker.js</code> and <code>picker.date.js</code>    in the <code>lib</code> folder.</p>
